{
  "doc_id": "4008",
  "text": "This study demonstrates the presence of SHM in BCL6 in 8 (62%) of 13 patients with PCLBCL, leg type, and 7 (37%) of 19 patients with PCFCL, and aberrant SHM in PAX5, RhoH/TTF, and/or MYC in 7 (54%) of 13 patients with PCLBCL, leg type, and 10 (53%) of 19 patients with PCFCL (Tables 1 and 2 ). The molecular profile of the detected mutations was similar in PCFCL and PCLBCL, leg type, and resembled the characteristics of mutations induced by the physiologic SHM process (Table S1 , available on the Blood website; see the Supplemental Tables link at the top of the online article). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] These data provide additional evidence that PCLBCL, leg type, and PCFCL are derived from germinal center experienced B cells.",
